# SQL Database Support

MUST gates when adding or planning support for a SQL engine. Full playbook: skill `sql-database-support`.

## 1. Classify first

| Kind | Examples | Implication |
|------|----------|-------------|
| Postgres-wire variant | TimescaleDB, Citus | Reuse `adapters/postgres`; focus on compose, seed, catalog quirks, specific tests |
| New dialect | MySQL, SQLite, … | New `adapters/<engine>` implementing `adapters.Adapter`; select in `app/app.go` (today hardcodes `postgres.New`) |

Do not treat a new dialect as compose-only.

## 2. No CI without analysis

`integration/<db>/DIFFERENCES.md` must exist before scaffolding CI green paths. Cover at least: image/init, catalog, DDL, wire/driver, system schemas/ACL, compose ownership vs Postgres.

## 3. Where matrix (condensed)

| Kind | Touch these | Do not |
|------|-------------|--------|
| Wire variant | `integration/<db>/` (compose, init, tests), `Makefile`, `test-integration-<db>.yml`, `DIFFERENCES.md` | New adapter; fold into Postgres compose |
| New dialect | ports in `adapters/*.go` if needed → `adapters/<engine>/` → `app/app.go` selection → config if needed → `make mockgen` → same integration/CI layout | Pretend compose-only; import engine from `controllers/` / `middlewares/` / `router/` |

## 4. Safety

- Parameterized SQL only; no unchecked identifier concatenation
- Auth / ACL / JWT / secrets fail closed — never weaken for “compatibility”
- No `postgres.Load()` or live DB outside `integration/` and startup (`cmd/`)

